WEBVTT

1
00:01:14.014 --> 00:01:18.182
(COUNTRY MUSIC PLAYING
ON CASSETTE PLAYER)

2
00:01:29.278 --> 00:01:30.519
(CASSETTE DISTORTING)

3
00:01:30.597 --> 00:01:31.929
(SCOFFS)

4
00:01:36.054 --> 00:01:37.346
(GASPS)
Jeez!

5
00:01:37.813 --> 00:01:38.880
(TIRES SCREECHING)

6
00:01:52.061 --> 00:01:53.795
(GASPING)

7
00:02:19.939 --> 00:02:21.607
SUSANNE:
With the community still shaken

8
00:02:21.674 --> 00:02:24.610
from last year's
Slater's Quarry tragedy.

9
00:02:24.677 --> 00:02:26.795
here in Boreham.
it's fresh heartache.

10
00:02:26.863 --> 00:02:28.280
As the search for
the missing women

11
00:02:28.349 --> 00:02:30.699
moves into the end
of its second day.

12
00:02:30.768 --> 00:02:35.904
hope is fading for Senator Kaplan's niece.
Juno. and her five friends.

13
00:02:35.990 --> 00:02:38.841
Just behind me I can see
one of the cave rescue teams

14
00:02:38.908 --> 00:02:40.074
emerging from the caverns.

15
00:02:40.143 --> 00:02:41.411
Good luck. guys.
Thanks.

16
00:02:41.478 --> 00:02:42.861
Chimney's pretty tight.
You all be careful in there.

17
00:02:42.937 --> 00:02:44.050
RESCUER: Will do.
SUSANNE: Sir.

18
00:02:44.117 --> 00:02:45.981
any signs of the missing women?

19
00:02:46.049 --> 00:02:47.049
(PEOPLE CLAMORING)

20
00:02:47.100 --> 00:02:49.586
Do you think you'll
find them alive?

21
00:02:49.652 --> 00:02:52.086
How does this compare to
Slater's Quarry?

22
00:02:54.207 --> 00:02:55.541
That's enough now.
Move back.

23
00:02:55.608 --> 00:02:57.726
Do you think you responded
quickly enough this time?

24
00:02:57.795 --> 00:02:59.661
Greg. leave it!
Greg!

25
00:03:02.565 --> 00:03:04.516
DAN:
We're back on in four hours.

26
00:03:04.585 --> 00:03:07.686
Get some sleep.
You too. boss.

27
00:03:07.754 --> 00:03:10.023
GREG: Hey. you want to
share a sleeping bag?

28
00:03:10.089 --> 00:03:12.025
(SNIFFING)
What's that cologne you're wearing?

29
00:03:12.091 --> 00:03:15.160
Yeah. six hours of sweat and dirt
and all other kinds of shit.

30
00:03:15.229 --> 00:03:16.528
I think I'll pass.

31
00:03:16.558 --> 00:03:19.214
(CELL PHONE RINGING)
Lynch? What's up?

32
00:03:22.218 --> 00:03:23.486
What?

33
00:03:25.221 --> 00:03:26.389
Where?

34
00:03:30.577 --> 00:03:32.961
Look. get a tracker dog
out there.

35
00:03:33.030 --> 00:03:35.081
See if you can find
where she came out.

36
00:03:35.915 --> 00:03:38.718
Yeah. all right. and...

37
00:03:38.786 --> 00:03:43.021
Let's keep the lid on this.
All right. I'm on my way to the hospital.

38
00:04:04.194 --> 00:04:05.311
VAINES:
Right. Doc. how is she?

39
00:04:05.379 --> 00:04:06.828
She's resting.

40
00:04:06.897 --> 00:04:08.498
We had to sedate her.

41
00:04:08.565 --> 00:04:10.183
I've got five girls missing

42
00:04:10.250 --> 00:04:11.984
and you put the one person
who knows where they are to sleep?

43
00:04:12.051 --> 00:04:14.921
She was hysterical.

44
00:04:14.989 --> 00:04:17.957
Besides. she has no memory
of the last two days.

45
00:04:18.025 --> 00:04:21.476
Whatever happened to her.
she's blanked it.

46
00:04:21.544 --> 00:04:22.592
Injuries?
Well.

47
00:04:22.650 --> 00:04:24.813
it's only some minor cuts and bruises.

48
00:04:24.881 --> 00:04:27.583
But her clothes were completely
stained in blood.

49
00:04:27.650 --> 00:04:29.201
So it's not her blood?

50
00:04:29.269 --> 00:04:30.502
No.

51
00:04:30.571 --> 00:04:32.137
But she's been in
a fight. all right.

52
00:04:32.205 --> 00:04:34.290
because judging
by her fingernails.

53
00:04:34.358 --> 00:04:37.410
she scratched some
big chunks out of somebody.

54
00:04:37.477 --> 00:04:39.045
Test her clothes.
get the blood type.

55
00:04:39.113 --> 00:04:40.446
Get the blood type of
the other five girls.

56
00:04:40.513 --> 00:04:42.132
Mmm-hmm.

57
00:04:44.968 --> 00:04:47.653
All right. let's see
what you can do.

58
00:04:54.677 --> 00:04:56.228
RIOS:
Hello. Sarah.

59
00:05:00.700 --> 00:05:03.953
I'm Jenna Rios from Hyde County
Sheriff's Department.

60
00:05:06.857 --> 00:05:08.758
This is Sheriff Vaines.

61
00:05:11.529 --> 00:05:12.962
How you feeling?

62
00:05:13.798 --> 00:05:15.765
Where am I?

63
00:05:15.833 --> 00:05:19.188
You're safe.
You're at Hyde County hospital.

64
00:05:20.755 --> 00:05:23.706
We've been searching
for you and your friends.

65
00:05:24.024 --> 00:05:25.590
two days ago

66
00:05:26.881 --> 00:05:28.978
you all set off on a caving expedition

67
00:05:29.046 --> 00:05:31.181
and you never came back.

68
00:05:32.082 --> 00:05:35.602
We've been following your
Boreham Cavern flight plan

69
00:05:35.669 --> 00:05:37.732
but we found nothing.

70
00:05:38.766 --> 00:05:40.777
Can you tell us what happened to you?

71
00:05:43.377 --> 00:05:46.845
I don't know.
I can't remember anything.

72
00:05:52.485 --> 00:05:56.856
Sarah. your friends
are still missing.

73
00:05:59.126 --> 00:06:01.678
We need you to
help us find them.

74
00:06:04.149 --> 00:06:05.814
Beth.

75
00:06:05.882 --> 00:06:06.975
RIOS:
Beth.

76
00:06:07.752 --> 00:06:09.619
What happened to Beth?

77
00:06:12.523 --> 00:06:14.356
What can you remember?

78
00:06:18.796 --> 00:06:20.413
What about Juno?

79
00:06:23.434 --> 00:06:24.751
Jessie.

80
00:06:26.319 --> 00:06:27.520
Where's Jessie?

81
00:06:27.589 --> 00:06:28.688
Your daughter?

82
00:06:32.993 --> 00:06:35.496
Sarah. Sarah.

83
00:06:37.031 --> 00:06:39.632
I need you to
listen to me carefully.

84
00:06:41.769 --> 00:06:44.188
Your daughter
isn't here. Sarah.

85
00:06:45.423 --> 00:06:47.489
She died.

86
00:06:47.558 --> 00:06:49.460
A year ago.
in Scotland.

87
00:06:49.527 --> 00:06:50.910
No.

88
00:06:52.463 --> 00:06:54.447
I know how hard
this must be for you.

89
00:06:54.515 --> 00:06:58.301
but you have to try...
No. no. No! No.

90
00:07:00.538 --> 00:07:01.688
DAN:
Come on.

91
00:07:16.370 --> 00:07:17.637
(DOG BARKING)

92
00:07:17.705 --> 00:07:19.806
(MEN CHATTERING)

93
00:07:45.349 --> 00:07:47.851
This looks like the
end of the trail.

94
00:07:50.588 --> 00:07:52.120
What's that?

95
00:07:52.189 --> 00:07:53.456
That there's
Chapel Mine.

96
00:08:00.097 --> 00:08:02.231
Cuffs. come here.
come here.

97
00:08:03.901 --> 00:08:05.569
Go find them. boy.

98
00:08:16.598 --> 00:08:17.864
One of these days
I'm gonna come up here

99
00:08:17.932 --> 00:08:20.151
and help myself to
some of this shit.

100
00:08:23.554 --> 00:08:26.524
What you found. boy?
What you found?

101
00:08:34.582 --> 00:08:35.749
Cuffs?

102
00:08:48.212 --> 00:08:50.197
(GROWLING)
Holy shit!

103
00:08:50.265 --> 00:08:51.916
(WHIMPERING)

104
00:08:59.440 --> 00:09:00.991
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

105
00:09:02.693 --> 00:09:04.544
Sheriff.
Dan.

106
00:09:04.613 --> 00:09:06.746
Keep it under your hat.
but we found one of the girls.

107
00:09:06.814 --> 00:09:08.748
Dog picked up her scent
near the old Chapel Mine.

108
00:09:08.816 --> 00:09:10.950
That's the other side of the county.
I know.

109
00:09:11.702 --> 00:09:13.386
Jeez.

110
00:09:13.454 --> 00:09:15.322
Don't tell me we've been looking
in the wrong place.

111
00:09:15.389 --> 00:09:17.558
Listen. I don't want to shift
the whole goddamn circus.

112
00:09:17.626 --> 00:09:20.295
I just want a couple of volunteers
to pick up where the dog left off.

113
00:09:21.796 --> 00:09:23.897
All right. give us an hour.

114
00:09:27.369 --> 00:09:29.987
DAN:
Cath. Greg. rise and shine.

115
00:09:30.072 --> 00:09:32.823
Blood on Sarah Carter's
clothes. A-positive.

116
00:09:33.442 --> 00:09:36.243
Juno Kaplan is A-positive.

117
00:09:36.310 --> 00:09:40.079
So? I'm A-positive.
Half the state is A-positive.

118
00:09:40.147 --> 00:09:41.298
Can she walk?

119
00:09:41.366 --> 00:09:42.500
Sure.

120
00:09:42.566 --> 00:09:44.118
Wait. wait. you're not seriously
gonna take her out...

121
00:09:44.186 --> 00:09:47.137
Rios. get her dressed
and get her in the car.

122
00:11:01.130 --> 00:11:02.413
(GRUNTING)

123
00:11:19.581 --> 00:11:21.916
ED:
My granddaddy used to work down there.

124
00:11:21.982 --> 00:11:23.551
One time. him and two of his buddies

125
00:11:23.618 --> 00:11:25.703
broke into a whole new cave system.

126
00:11:25.771 --> 00:11:28.573
Really big.

127
00:11:28.640 --> 00:11:32.326
Company bosses figured there
should be some rich pickings to be had.

128
00:11:32.394 --> 00:11:36.480
so they sent my granddaddy back down
to have a good look-see.

129
00:11:36.548 --> 00:11:39.516
He never come back.

130
00:11:39.752 --> 00:11:43.220
Folks reckoned they must've broke
clean through into hell.

131
00:11:44.489 --> 00:11:47.491
The devil was mighty pissed.

132
00:11:47.559 --> 00:11:51.779
So you're telling me that there's an
uncharted cave system down there?

133
00:11:53.398 --> 00:11:55.683
Cool.

134
00:11:55.752 --> 00:11:58.686
There's a map of
the mines here.

135
00:11:58.755 --> 00:12:01.807
If the caves are uncharted.
we won't even know where to begin.

136
00:12:01.873 --> 00:12:04.325
Bring the girl.

137
00:12:04.426 --> 00:12:08.512
Come on. Dan. she's the only
one been down there.

138
00:12:08.580 --> 00:12:10.681
All we gotta do is get a nod from her.
left or right.

139
00:12:10.749 --> 00:12:12.350
Narrows the search.

140
00:12:12.417 --> 00:12:14.952
There's a mountain full of caves
and fuck-all time.

141
00:12:15.019 --> 00:12:16.787
Could piggyback on
the elevator cables.

142
00:12:16.855 --> 00:12:18.889
(CHUCKLES)

143
00:12:18.907 --> 00:12:22.026
You planning to go down there.
why not go down there in style?

144
00:12:22.110 --> 00:12:24.562
What. this old shit
still works?

145
00:12:24.629 --> 00:12:26.330
Sonny. let me tell you.

146
00:12:26.398 --> 00:12:27.833
this old shit-bucket
will be working

147
00:12:27.899 --> 00:12:30.985
long time after
that MP3 of yours.

148
00:12:31.053 --> 00:12:32.536
Whatever.

149
00:12:32.604 --> 00:12:35.123
All right. Ed.
get it going.

150
00:12:39.277 --> 00:12:42.646
RIOS: I'm sorry. but Mommy's
got to help people tonight.

151
00:12:42.714 --> 00:12:46.767
Chica. when Grandma tells you to go to bed.
you go to bed. okay?

152
00:12:47.587 --> 00:12:51.238
Honey. I love you.

153
00:12:53.041 --> 00:12:55.694
Okay. baby. I'll see you
tomorrow. okay?

154
00:12:58.213 --> 00:13:02.082
Rios. get yourself kitted and
get her kitted. We're going down.

155
00:13:09.975 --> 00:13:13.744
RIOS:
Okay. Sarah. I know this is difficult.

156
00:13:13.812 --> 00:13:17.047
but if you do this.
it could help jog your memory.

157
00:13:18.483 --> 00:13:20.402
Your friends could still be alive.

158
00:13:20.470 --> 00:13:22.636
You have to help us find them.

159
00:13:30.630 --> 00:13:32.012
(WHIRRING)

160
00:13:34.283 --> 00:13:36.383
CATH:
Hey. Sarah. this might fit you.

161
00:13:39.522 --> 00:13:42.057
DAN:
You want to lose that heavy metal.

162
00:13:42.125 --> 00:13:44.609
Gun blast down
there'd be like dynamite.

163
00:13:44.676 --> 00:13:46.994
Come on. I'll put them in the car.

164
00:13:47.062 --> 00:13:49.013
My gun stays with me.

165
00:13:53.251 --> 00:13:55.237
This is a missing
persons case.

166
00:13:55.304 --> 00:13:58.105
What the hell do you think
you're gonna find down there?

167
00:13:58.174 --> 00:13:59.191
(ENGINE STARTING)

168
00:14:20.178 --> 00:14:21.346
GIRL: (WHISPERING)
Mummy.

169
00:14:22.247 --> 00:14:23.949
Right. let's get moving.

170
00:14:34.260 --> 00:14:35.994
Come on.

171
00:14:36.061 --> 00:14:37.162
(INHALES SHARPLY)

172
00:14:41.317 --> 00:14:42.551
You all ready to ride?

173
00:14:42.617 --> 00:14:44.152
Yeah. let's do it.

174
00:15:22.475 --> 00:15:24.042
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

175
00:15:29.098 --> 00:15:30.265
(MACHINE CREAKING)

176
00:15:45.214 --> 00:15:46.247
(THUDDING)

177
00:15:46.366 --> 00:15:47.448
(GASPING)
Whoa!

178
00:15:57.460 --> 00:15:59.094
(EXCLAIMING)

179
00:16:35.848 --> 00:16:37.548
(CREAKING)

180
00:16:43.639 --> 00:16:44.806
VAINES:
Jesus.

181
00:16:57.035 --> 00:16:58.754
DAN:
Hang on. just wait up a second.

182
00:16:58.821 --> 00:17:00.005
(COUGHS)

183
00:17:06.329 --> 00:17:07.979
Here. drink this.

184
00:17:10.350 --> 00:17:13.386
She's okay.
Let me worry about her.

185
00:17:15.855 --> 00:17:18.675
Come on. Dan.
let's get to the goddamn cave.

186
00:17:19.926 --> 00:17:23.628
Listen. Down here.
I call the shots.

187
00:17:24.597 --> 00:17:26.331
Is that understood?

188
00:17:27.300 --> 00:17:28.834
Loud and clear.

189
00:17:30.253 --> 00:17:31.604
Let's go.

190
00:17:51.808 --> 00:17:52.823
(GASPS)

191
00:18:16.299 --> 00:18:18.617
DAN:
Should be a ladder down there.

192
00:18:20.720 --> 00:18:23.239
How long have I
been teaching you?

193
00:18:25.425 --> 00:18:27.393
Your light is your life.

194
00:18:29.696 --> 00:18:30.813
Hey.

195
00:18:32.716 --> 00:18:35.985
All right. Okay. we've gotta go
down another level.

196
00:18:37.304 --> 00:18:38.353
Greg.

197
00:18:49.766 --> 00:18:52.134
You gotta be
fucking kidding me.

198
00:19:06.583 --> 00:19:08.250
(CREAKING)

199
00:19:18.311 --> 00:19:19.912
Is it okay?

200
00:19:19.979 --> 00:19:23.181
You know what's good?
Modern mines have metal props.

201
00:19:24.551 --> 00:19:26.786
Miners prefer
these old wooden ones.

202
00:19:26.853 --> 00:19:28.670
Why's that?

203
00:19:28.738 --> 00:19:32.342
The metal ones don't give you any
warning when they're about to go.

204
00:19:36.512 --> 00:19:38.464
(RUMBLING)

205
00:19:40.401 --> 00:19:41.734
(SCOFFS)
After you.

206
00:19:51.679 --> 00:19:54.514
DAN: Okay. we should hit the
cave system somewhere up here.

207
00:19:54.581 --> 00:19:56.617
Greg. go scout ahead.

208
00:19:56.684 --> 00:19:57.934
You got it.

209
00:20:00.120 --> 00:20:03.624
DAN: And Cath. you're next.
Deputy.

210
00:20:13.933 --> 00:20:15.902
GREG:
I think I've found it.

211
00:20:19.757 --> 00:20:21.624
What the hell is that?

212
00:20:23.127 --> 00:20:24.761
It's a pit pony.

213
00:20:27.947 --> 00:20:29.682
Always a good sign.

214
00:20:29.750 --> 00:20:31.718
(CHUCKLING)

215
00:20:31.784 --> 00:20:33.252
(CRASHING)

216
00:20:48.419 --> 00:20:51.889
GREG:
Check it out. This is awesome.

217
00:21:14.895 --> 00:21:17.095
Greg. T.I.

218
00:21:19.932 --> 00:21:23.086
Hey. hey. Don't...
Don't touch anything.

219
00:21:23.153 --> 00:21:25.888
This place is
thousands of years old.

220
00:21:27.508 --> 00:21:28.991
Well. you're hot.

221
00:21:29.059 --> 00:21:31.159
(SCOFFS)
Get away.

222
00:21:31.228 --> 00:21:35.465
Sarah. do you
recognize anything?

223
00:21:56.954 --> 00:21:57.954
(GASPS)

224
00:21:58.022 --> 00:21:59.189
What?

225
00:22:32.506 --> 00:22:34.224
(SCREAMS)

226
00:22:37.428 --> 00:22:40.413
It's okay. It's okay.
she just got spooked.

227
00:22:51.041 --> 00:22:52.676
Calcium deposits.

228
00:22:55.347 --> 00:22:56.913
Let's keep moving.

229
00:22:56.982 --> 00:22:58.631
It's okay. come on.
Come on.

230
00:23:13.414 --> 00:23:14.447
Come on.

231
00:23:24.074 --> 00:23:25.224
Come on. Sheriff.
you can do it.

232
00:23:25.292 --> 00:23:27.076
I ain't that old yet.

233
00:23:34.703 --> 00:23:36.052
Which way?

234
00:23:38.889 --> 00:23:40.456
You recognize this?

235
00:23:43.628 --> 00:23:45.446
Cath. have a listen.

236
00:24:11.406 --> 00:24:12.640
(STATIC)

237
00:24:38.299 --> 00:24:39.515
Anything?

238
00:24:39.583 --> 00:24:42.336
I don't know.
I think I hear something.

239
00:25:11.683 --> 00:25:12.934
(GASPS)

240
00:25:22.043 --> 00:25:23.127
Jesus!

241
00:25:23.194 --> 00:25:25.229
Oh. my God!
VAINES: Shit!

242
00:25:25.297 --> 00:25:27.548
Fuck! Sarah.
Look at me.

243
00:25:29.701 --> 00:25:30.917
VAINES:
She's moving.

244
00:25:30.985 --> 00:25:33.587
No. There's no body heat.
It's not possible.

245
00:25:38.960 --> 00:25:40.478
(CATH SCREAMING)

246
00:25:47.035 --> 00:25:48.235
Deputy.

247
00:25:48.303 --> 00:25:49.703
(SARAH VOMITING)

248
00:25:49.771 --> 00:25:51.171
Okay.
Sarah.

249
00:25:58.379 --> 00:26:01.666
She's been butchered.

250
00:26:01.733 --> 00:26:05.936
Six girls came down to this cave.
One came out.

251
00:26:06.004 --> 00:26:07.606
Covered in her friends' blood.

252
00:26:07.673 --> 00:26:10.908
Now. you tell me what the hell
happened down here.

253
00:26:10.909 --> 00:26:12.793
(STAMMERS) Wait a second. You think
she had something to do with this?

254
00:26:12.860 --> 00:26:14.528
This is fucked up!
Dan. get your team out of my face.

255
00:26:14.596 --> 00:26:16.096
Man. you brought her down...
Get off my back!

256
00:26:16.164 --> 00:26:17.831
Greg! Save it.

